args: I knew it! Yer Gauld the Bloodfist!
No idea what you're on about.
Don't play dumb with me, old timer.\nThat fake arm there's a dead giveaway.
I came here to find you.\nYou don't belong in a mine.
I'm a miner.\nWhere else am I supposed to crack rocks?

Sakes alive, but yer a stubborn old ox.
Yer old Bloodfist woulda torn itself off
and run away if ya tried to use it to
dig up a buncha old boulders!
Nothing bloody about this limb of mine—\nand it works just fine for the job I do.
Are you serious? C'mon now, we all\nknow the story of the old Bloodfist.\nA real crimson puncher, that one!
Hell yeah! Let's see that arm'a yers\npainted red again, old timer!
You belong at his side, ya know.\n...C'mon, ya know who I'm talkin' about!
Flap your jaws till your head flies off.\nI still don't have a clue.
Fine. If yer gonna play stupid, I'll just\nhave ya show me what's under that\nbushy beard'a yers.
Looks like you've made a point to grow\nit nice and long to hide the ＂sign,＂ but\nhiding it won't make it go away, old man.
If ya want me to stop, admit who you\nare and come with me to see him.\nOtherwise...
Otherwise what? You think you can\nhandle what I'll dish out?
If it's the story of the Bloodfist ya want,\nI'll give it to ya WITH A DEMONSTRATION,\nya cockle-headed daisypusher!
You sure you wanna do that, old timer?\nI'm with HIM, after all.
If you were gonna hide behind yer mama's\nskirts when things got hot, you shoulda\ntold me that from the get-go!
Now get the hell outta here—and tell HIM\nthat my place is here now, got it?!
Ain't smart to turn him down, old timer.\nAin't smart at all.
That the new guy just now?
Guess I hazed him a little hard.\nHe up and quit on the spot.
Saint and bejabbers, Gauld! I told ya not\nto be breakin' out the death stare again!
I know, I know. It's just when my blood\nstarts to boil, I only know one way to\nget my point across.
I thought I'd changed since the old days,\nbut maybe that's a fool's dream...
...Never mind me. Let's get back to work.
Welcome home, Gramps!\nAre you done working for today?
I sure am, darling. And what a lucky fellow\nI am to have you to cheer me up after a\nlong day in the mines.
Hee hee! Your beard is all messy.\nLet me wipe it off.
Angie! Oh darling, I'm so sorry!
Hush now. I'm the one who did wrong.
I'm the one who did wrong...
So we found him at last, eh?
Sure did, boss! It was Gauld the Bloodfist,\nbig as life'n twice as ugly.
H-he wouldn't come. Didn't want to, like.\nI figured it was best to run back and\nletcha know quick as I could.
I didn't order you to ＂figure＂ what was best.\nI ordered you to bring him to me.\nWas I not clear?
Take him away. I got no use for a fool\nthat don't know how to listen.
Boss, no! I did my best for ya!
Lemme go, ya clods! Lemme... NOOOOO!
This ain't some sweet little club where\nya get extra points for ＂doin' yer best!＂
Which makes us the perfect match\nfor the Bloodfist. Geh heh heh...
